nit: you can return here, then you don't need the "else" branch
Seems reasonable but would like those error traces that got deleted
Maybe use template function type to be consistent with bmcweb code?

> Maybe use template function type to be consistent with bmcweb code?

There is no stronger requirement to use template or std::function here, I tend to use std::function because its callback parameters are well known.

> Why not just use MapperGetSubTreePathsResponse ?

No, That's not the right way, although they describe the same attributes, but their meanings are completely different, that's a lazy way 😊
Can we do the `ec` check inside the `callback` to align with the surrounding codes?
nit: suggest to move the line lambda function into a separate function.

> nit: suggest to move the line lambda function into a separate function.

Ed suggest
```
Either leave it the way it is as an rvalue, or move it over to the new pattern of a normal method.
```
I choose to keep rvalue
Is it possible to just return and don't set the internal error if the `dbus::utility::MapperEndPoints` container is empty?

> Is it possible to just return and don't set the internal error if the `dbus::utility::MapperEndPoints` container is empty?

Sorry, This commit just refactors the getAssociaitonEndPoints method without paying attention to its function, and I will not change the logic of the original author to implement it.
